<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note5" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref5
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">5</A>
The festival of Bona Dea, from which all men were excluded.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note6" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">6</A>
The towns beyond the river Po, such as Verona, Comum, and Cremona, wished to obtain the rights of <SPAN CLASS="whole">citizen</SPAN>&shy;ship, which had been given to many of the Italian towns at the close of the Social War (89‑88 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note7" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref7
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">7</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Forum ornare</SPAN> was the technical term for the display there by the aediles of the material to be used in their public shows.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note8" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">8</A>
As <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">iudex quaestionis</SPAN>, an office held by Caesar between the <SPAN CLASS="whole">aedile</SPAN>&shy;ship and the <SPAN CLASS="whole">praetor</SPAN>&shy;ship.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note9" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref9
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">9</A>
As <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">iudex perduellionis</SPAN>, or <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">duumvir perduellionis</SPAN>, one of a commission of two men appointed to try cases of high treason. Of these one was selected by lot (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">sorte ductus</SPAN>) to conduct the trial, if one were necessary, and pass sentence. An appeal was allowed and the duumvir then brought the case before the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">comitia centuriata</SPAN> (in the regal period before the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">comitia curiata</SPAN>). See
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/livy/liv.1.shtml#26
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Liv. 1.26.5 ff.</A>;
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/rabirio.shtml#4
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Cic. <I>Rab.</I> 4</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note10" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref10
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">10</A>
As governor of Egypt; see
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#11
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. xi</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note11" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref11
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">11</A>
Namely, Gnaeus Pompeius.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note12" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref12
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">12</A>
When the consuls went to the Capitol to offer sacrifice at the commencement of their term of office (on January 1), their friends escorted them to the temple and back to their homes. Caesar took advantage of the absence of the aristocrats for his attack on Catulus.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note13" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref13
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">13</A>
Novius seems to have been <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quaesitor</SPAN>, a special commissioner appointed to conduct the investigation (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quaestio</SPAN>) of the Catilinarian conspiracy; perhaps we should read <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">quaesitorem</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note14" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref14
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">14</A>
That is, without waiting for the decrees of the senate which formally confirmed the appointments of the new governors, and provided them with funds and equipment.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note15" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref15
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">15</A>
If <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">silvae callesque</SPAN> should stand in the text, it is used in a different sense from <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">calles</SPAN> in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/4B*.html#27
	"TARGET="Tacitus_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Tacitus,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Tac. <I>Ann.</I> 4.27</A>. It seems to designate provinces where the duties of the governor would be confined to guarding the <SPAN CLASS="whole">mountain-pastures</SPAN> and keeping the woods free from brigands. The senate would not run the risk of letting Caesar secure a province involving the command of an army. <I>Cf.</I> note on xxiv.1<!-- DON'T LINK: see my note immediately following: -->.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
Thayer's Note: Although the subject of chapter xxiv is germane, there is no note on
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#24
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
xxiv.1, <I>q.v.</I></A>
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note16" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref16
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">16</A>
Business could be interrupted or postponed at Rome by the announcement of an augur or a magistrate that he had seen a flash of lightning or some other adverse sign; sometimes an opponent merely announced that he would "watch the skies" for such omens.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note17" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref17
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">17</A>
Torrentius put <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">per iocum</SPAN> after <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">signarent</SPAN>, but such jesting would not be tolerated in actual legal documents.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note18" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref18
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">18</A>
Through a special commission of twenty men.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note19" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref19
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">19</A>
By making a speech of several hours' duration;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Gellius/4*.html#10.8
	"TARGET="Gellius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EPlusL,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Gell. 4.10.8</A>. The senate arose in a body and escorted Cato to prison, and Caesar was forced to release him.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note20" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref20
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">20</A>
For his conduct during the war with Mithridates.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note21" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref21
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">21</A>
That is, after the close of the business day, an indication of the haste with which the adoption was rushed through.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note22" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref22
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">22</A>
Used in a double sense, the second unmentionable.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note23" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref23
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">23</A>
A Celtic word meaning a crested lark,
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Pliny_the_Elder/11*.html#37
	"TARGET="Pliny"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Pliny,WIDTH,205)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Plin. <I>N. H.</I> 11.37)
	</A>
which was the device on the helmets of the legion.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0">
Thayer's Note: For comprehensive details and sources, see the article
		<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Alauda.html
		"TARGET="princeps"
