in Smith's <I>Dictionary of Greek and Roman Antiquities</I>, and the further articles linked there. The modern American reader can imagine something very much like a float at the Rose Bowl.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note64" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Julius*.html#ref64
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">64</A>
Playing on the double meaning of <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">cor</SPAN>, also regarded as the seat of intelligence.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
